physical_examinations.relevant_findings: General: Alert, oriented x3, no acute distress; Neurological: Pain well controlled; Lungs: Clear to auscultation bilaterally; Heart: Regular rate and rhythm, no murmurs/rubs/gallops; Abdomen: Non-distended, soft, tender to epigastric and right upper quadrant palpation; No guarding or rebound; Bowel sounds: 1+; Extremities: Dorsalis pedis and other pulses 2+, no cyanosis/clubbing/edema.
